<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="257" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="257">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="257">
See 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4081/BollettinoSEI.2017.55" author="Bassi, G" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, Genova" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" pagination="55 - 57" refId="B2" refString="Bassi, G, 2017. Descrizione di una nuova Catoptria Huebner, 1825 dell'Italia centrale, con note sul suo gruppo-specie di appartenenza (Lepidoptera: Pyraloidea, Crambidae, Crambinae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, Genova 149 (2): 55 - 57, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4081/BollettinoSEI.2017.55" title="Descrizione di una nuova Catoptria Huebner, 1825 dell'Italia centrale, con note sul suo gruppo-specie di appartenenza (Lepidoptera: Pyraloidea, Crambidae, Crambinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4081/BollettinoSEI.2017.55" volume="149" year="2017">Bassi (2017</bibRefCitation>
: 55); Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Catoptria spp., female genitalia 19 C. samnitica sp. nov., paratype, GS 5751 GB 20 C. samnitica sp. nov., paratype, GS 6265 GB 21 C. samnitica sp. nov., paratype, GS 6292 GB 22 C. spatulellus (Turati), Italy, Emilia, Pievepelago, GS 6227 GB 23 C. spatulellus (Turati), Italy, Emilia, Gabellina, GS 2339 GB 24 C. spatulellus (Turati), Italy, Tuscany, Corfino, GS 6692 GB 25 C. apenninica Bassi, Italy, Latium, Monte Terminillo, GS 6669 GB 26 C. europaeica Bleszynski, France, Alpes Maritimes, PN Mercantour, Col de la Moutiere, GS 6653 GB. Not to scale." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.43.52520.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439146" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">25</figureCitation>
shows female genitalia variation compared with the holotype (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4081/BollettinoSEI.2017.55" author="Bassi, G" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, Genova" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" pagination="55 - 57" refId="B2" refString="Bassi, G, 2017. Descrizione di una nuova Catoptria Huebner, 1825 dell'Italia centrale, con note sul suo gruppo-specie di appartenenza (Lepidoptera: Pyraloidea, Crambidae, Crambinae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, Genova 149 (2): 55 - 57, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4081/BollettinoSEI.2017.55" title="Descrizione di una nuova Catoptria Huebner, 1825 dell'Italia centrale, con note sul suo gruppo-specie di appartenenza (Lepidoptera: Pyraloidea, Crambidae, Crambinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4081/BollettinoSEI.2017.55" volume="149" year="2017">Bassi 2017</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3) and with 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. europaeica" pageId="4" pageNumber="257" rank="species" species="europaeica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">C. europaeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Bleszynski, S" journalOrPublisher="Georg Fromme &amp; Co., Wien" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refId="B4" refString="Bleszynski, S, 1965. Crambinae. In: Amsel HG, Gregor F, Reisser H (Eds) Microlepidoptera Palaearctica 1(1-2). Georg Fromme &amp; Co., Wien" title="Crambinae. In: Amsel HG, Gregor F, Reisser H (Eds) Microlepidoptera Palaearctica 1 (1 - 2)." year="1965">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Błeszyński">Bleszynski</normalizedToken>
1965
</bibRefCitation>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Catoptria spp., female genitalia 19 C. samnitica sp. nov., paratype, GS 5751 GB 20 C. samnitica sp. nov., paratype, GS 6265 GB 21 C. samnitica sp. nov., paratype, GS 6292 GB 22 C. spatulellus (Turati), Italy, Emilia, Pievepelago, GS 6227 GB 23 C. spatulellus (Turati), Italy, Emilia, Gabellina, GS 2339 GB 24 C. spatulellus (Turati), Italy, Tuscany, Corfino, GS 6692 GB 25 C. apenninica Bassi, Italy, Latium, Monte Terminillo, GS 6669 GB 26 C. europaeica Bleszynski, France, Alpes Maritimes, PN Mercantour, Col de la Moutiere, GS 6653 GB. Not to scale." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.43.52520.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439146" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">26</figureCitation>
). Like the females the males are also smaller (on average 25-26 mm) than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. europaeica" pageId="4" pageNumber="257" rank="species" species="europaeica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">C. europaeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(on average 28-30 mm). In the forewing the medial band of the longitudinal streak is darker and slightly larger, along the costa the subapical dot is larger and extending closer to the apex, and the fringes are white, tipped brown as opposed to white with medial and apical grey brown bands in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. europaeica" pageId="4" pageNumber="257" rank="species" species="europaeica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">C. europaeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The hind wing is brown as opposed to pale grey brown in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. europaeica" pageId="4" pageNumber="257" rank="species" species="europaeica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">C. europaeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
